name: Dynamics CRM On Premise
description: Add a Microsoft Dynamics CRM Instance to connect your existing Microsoft Dynamics CRM account to the CRM Hub, allowing you to manage contacts, leads, accounts, opportunities etc. across multiple CRM Elements. You will need your Microsoft Dynamics CRM account information to add an instance.
configDescription: Microsoft Dynamics CRM On Prem IFD with NTLM Authentication

configuration.name: Bulk Date Format
configuration.description: The date format for use by the bulk APIs

configuration.name: Allow Select Fields parameter
configuration.description: Enables use of global fields query parameter to filter response to only specified fields. This will override any existing vendor functionality on the connector

configuration.name: Bulk Query Modified Time Attribute
configuration.description: The field or attribute for the last modified time for use by the bulk APIs

configuration.name: Bulk Query Create Time Attribute
configuration.description: The field or attribute for the created time for use by the bulk APIs

configuration.name: Dynamics CRM URL to the ODATA service
configuration.description: The full url of your OrganizationData.Svc

configuration.name: Filter null values from the response
configuration.description: Used to enable/disable filtering of null values from the responses.

configuration.name: Default select fields
configuration.description: Generic map used to specify default fields for bulk download and GET /all requests. Each key should be the canonical objectName and values may be specified as a comma-delimited string or a list of strings

configuration.name: Event Notifications Enabled

configuration.name: Event poller refresh interval
configuration.description: Used for how often to poll the application (in minutes)

configuration.name: Callback Notification Signature Key
